<p>Okay, let's see... <br /> <br />A good charmed warrior type pet will crush the dps of a summoned pet. In another recent post, I mention that I like to charm duo razorfiends in the Plane of Valor. They can hit for over 400 a pop. The previously-mentioned Vxed pets do hit for 1.2k a pop... you will not find a summoned pet that can hope to keep up with that. Not to mention that they have MUCH more hp. <br /> <br />A charmed caster can be a bit of a gamble... they tend, at higher levels, to have several different spells. Some are smarter about what they'll cast, but, often, they'll still try to cast a lot until they run out of mana. Kind of annoying when you charm a shadowknight pet for it's melee damage and it spends part of the fight trying to land a snare or lifetap, for example. <br />I've never dealt much with healer pets, but I'd wager they'd waste a lot of time and mana healing wounds that don't really need to be healed. <br /> <br />Mobs keep their stats in any expansion or zone created before Gates of Discord. Even GoD mobs keep most of their stats, altho they often lose something while charmed, like the ability to flurry. Mobs in Omens of War or later expansions or zones created after OoW get greatly reduced stats when charmed (usually losing abilities like flurry or rampage, and hitting for much less... it's a sad thing to charm a mob that hits for 1k, only to have it hit for 200 while charmed), but jump right back to their normal stats when charm breaks, making charm in later expansions a big hassle and just not worth the effort except in rare encounters where charm is part of the solution (certain raid encounters), since the first thing they'll want to do on charm break is eat you alive. <br /> <br />If a mob is kept charmed, it will block that spawn point from spawning any other mobs until that mob is dead.</p>
